This directory contains data that is derived from JRA55-do (JRA-55 based surface 
data set for driving ocean-sea ice models). 

We are in the process of writing a terms of use of this dataset, in the meantime 
refer to the JRA55-do license in /g/data1/ua8/JRA55-do/Terms_of_Use.txt

The Repeat Year Forcing (RYF) data (also known as Repeat Annual Forcing (RAF)), is
part of an effort to produce a single year of meteorological forcing data that can
be used to spin-up an ocean model with as few biases as possible. This is analagous
to the Core II Normal Year Forcing (CNYF).

The repeat year is the May 1 - April 31 period mapped onto a single year. April
to December is joined to the end of the January to May to create a single year with
a discontinuity at April 31/May 1. This minimises the shock the model experiences
as it is a calm period of the annual climate cycle.

Three "years" were identified by examining common climate metrics. These are 1984/85,
1990/91 and 2003/2004.

When a year contained a leap day on the 29th of February the corresponding April 31
was removed to create a 365 day year.

The code used to accomplish this is here:

https://github.com/aidanheerdegen/make_ryf/commit/968edae060b7021128442ef0e0bb46db91170fc0


